first_para: Annette Lesley Brooke, OBE, MP, PC (born 7 June 1947), née Kelly, is a British Liberal Democrat politician.

full.extract:
Annette Lesley Brooke, OBE, MP, PC (born 7 June 1947), née Kelly, is a British Liberal Democrat politician.
She was the Member of Parliament (MP) for Mid Dorset and North Poole from 2001 to the dissolution of the 55th Parliament on 30 March 2015. At the time she left office, Brooke was the longest serving female MP in the history of the Liberal Democrats.
full.title: Annette Brooke
